wikipedia_page.main: Oscar Hermann Duhst (11 November 1872 – 31 August 1942) was an Australian politician who represented the South Australian House of Assembly multi-member seat of Wooroora from 1912 to 1915 representing the Liberal Union.

response: A new bridge was opened on 14 August 1914 by the Commissioner of Crown Lands, F. W. Young, accompanied by the other members of parliament for Wooroora, Oscar Duhst and David James and the chairman of the district council, Mr. F. McArdle.
